20:in noun phrases that contain other determiners (my house, this cat, America's history), although one can combine articles with iners).
21:with pronouns (he, nobody), although again certain combinations are possible (as the one, the many, the few).
22-preceding noun phrases consisting of a clause or infinitive phrase (what you've done is very good, to surrender is to die).
